        "frequency": "quarterly"
      }
    ],
    "methodology": "Possession claims data are from MoJ court statistics covering England and Wales. Arrears figures are UK Finance estimates of residential mortgages with arrears equivalent to 2.5% or more of the outstanding balance (significant arrears). Mortgage rates are Bank of England quoted rates for new 2-year fixed-rate mortgages at 75% LTV, averaged quarterly. The 2020 dip in possession claims reflects the court closures and eviction moratorium during the COVID-19 pandemic, not an improvement in borrower circumstances.",
    "knownIssues": [
      "Possession claims dropped to near-zero during 2020-Q2 due to COVID court closures and the eviction moratorium — this is a policy artefact, not a sign of reduced distress.",
      "Arrears figures may understate true distress as lender forbearance measures (payment holidays, term extensions, interest-only concessions) keep some borrowers out of formal arrears categories.",
      "Mortgage rate data uses 75% LTV products; higher LTV borrowers (including many first-time buyers) face rates 0.3–0.8 percentage points higher.",
      "Pre-2015 arrears data uses a slightly different methodology (CML rather than UK Finance reporting); figures are broadly comparable but not directly continuous."
    ]
  }
